Envolve Capital is a licensed fund management company, specializing in renewable energy investments in the Baltic States, Poland and Central Europe with investor commitments over €170m and four active funds launched yet. As one of the leading fund managers in the region focused on renewable energy, we have access to top tier investors and exciting investment opportunities in an asset class, experiencing rapid development and growth throughout the world. 
We are a team of highly skilled professionals with expertise in investment management, M&A, capital raising and technical know-how. Key team members have led some of the most significant renewable energy transactions in the region, attracting leading global asset managers.
Our aim to accelerate the region‘s transition to renewable and sustainable energy by empowering local renewable energy developers and creating an institutional-level investment platform.
Your key responsibilities would be:
Analyze fund’s assets financial data, generate management reports for management review and propose ways to enhance asset performance;
Work closely with the accounting team to ensure accurate financial reporting;
Lead financial audit and fund’s asset valuation process;
Manage day-to-day interactions with external service providers or lenders;
Cash flow management, preparation of budgets and financial modeling;
Covenants calculation (bank reporting).
University degree in Economics; 
Work experience in financial analysis at least 2 years; 
Work experience in renewables asset management would be a benefit; 
Strong analytical skills and attention to details; 
Ability to work independently and as part of a team to achieve project goals; 
Excellent English language skills. 
Competitive pay and a package of additional benefits; 
Culture of fast pace, growth and challenges; 
And most important – freedom to think outside the box, create and implement your ideas; 
Career opportunities within the businesses of Modus Group. 
Monthly salary:
1500 - 2500 EUR net. Specific amount will be offered based on your work experience and competencies.

We currently have a vacancy for a Project Manager fluent in English, to offer his/her services as an expert who will be based in Brussels, Belgium. The work will be carried out either on the company’s premises or on site at the customer premises. In the context of the first assignment, the successful candidate will be integrated in the Development team of the company that will closely cooperate with a major client’s IT team on site.
Your tasks
Manage the implementation of information systems to meet identified business needs, acquiring and using the necessary resources and skills, within agreed parameters of cost, timescales, and quality;
Give proposals for project strategies, planning, definition of tasks and deliverables, review of project deliverables, quality control, risk analysis and management, status reports, problem reporting and management systems, follow up and organization;
Guide the team in charge of project activities and review their deliverables;
Participate in functional working groups and progress meetings;
Estimate costs, timescales and resource requirements for the successful completion of each project to agreed terms of reference;
Prepare and maintain project and quality plans and tracks activities against the plan, provide regular and accurate reports;
Monitor costs, timescales and resources used. Act where these deviate from agreed tolerances. Ensure that delivered systems are implemented within these criteria;
Manage the change control procedure gaining agreement for revisions to the project from project sponsors;
Provide effective leadership for the project team ensuring that team members are motivated and constantly developing their skills and experience.
University degree in IT or relevant discipline, combined with minimum 17 years of relevant working experience in IT;
At least 8 years of management of IT projects using project management methodologies such as Prince2, PMI, PM2, etc;
At least 6 years of experience with project management tools (e.g. MS-Project, JIRA ...);
At least 6 years of experience with Agile (e.g. SCRUM, Kanban, etc.);
At least 1 year of experience with web services (e.g. SOAP, REST);
At least 1 year of experience with interoperable solutions;
At least 2 years of experience with web applications;
At least 2 years of experience with Object-Oriented development;
Experience in management of technical teams and translating user needs into technical requirements;
Good knowledge of project management standards and methodologies (Project Scheduling, Strategic Planning, Financial Modelling, Budgeting, Forecasting, Performance Tracking);
The following certifications would be considered as assets: Project Management Professional (PMP), PRINCE2 Foundation/PRINCE2 Practitioner, Certified in PM2 and Business Analyst – BABOK;
Excellent command of the English language.
If you are seeking a career in an exciting and dynamic company, where you will offer your services as part of a team of a major European Institution, operating in an international, multilingual and multicultural environment where you can expect real chances to make a difference, please send us your detailed CV in English, quoting reference (19527/02/2026).
We offer a competitive remuneration (either on contract basis or remuneration with full benefits package), based on qualifications and experience. All applications will be treated as confidential. 
EUROPEAN DYNAMICS (ED) (www.eurodyn.com) is a leading Software, Information and Communication Technologies company, operating internationally (Athens, Brussels, Luxembourg, Copenhagen, Stockholm, London, Nicosia, Hong-Kong, Valetta, etc). The company employs over 1000 engineers, IT experts and consultants (around 3% PhD, 36% MSc and 53% BSc or equivalent). We design and develop software applications using state-of-the-art technology. The group generates annual revenues in the range of EURO 40 million, with an EBITDA in the range of 20%. The value of our contract portfolio exceeds EURO 250 million. EUROPEAN DYNAMICS is a renowned supplier of IT services to government institutions, multinational corporations, public administrations and multinational companies, research and academic institutes.
As part of our dedication to the diversity of our workforce, we are committed to Equal Employment Opportunity without regard for race, color, national origin, ethnicity, gender, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, or religion.
EUROPEAN DYNAMICS (ED) adheres to the General Data Protection Regulation principles by applying its Privacy Policy as published in www.eurodyn.com/privacy. By submitting an application to this position and by sharing your personal data with ED, you acknowledge and accept its Policy and authorise ED to process your personal data for the purposes of the company's recruitment opportunities, in line to the Policy.

About the Team

We are Quadcode, a fintech company excelling in financial brokerage activities and delivering advanced financial products to our global clientele. Our flagship product, an internal trading platform, is offered as a Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) solution to other brokers.

We are Quadcode, a fintech company that develops a SaaS trading platform for clients around the world. 
Our business is structured into specialized units to ensure sustainable growth and operational excellence.

One of our key business units is IQ Option — a globally recognized financial broker, known for its innovative online trading platform. Founded in 2013, IQ Option has become one of the leading platforms in online trading, operating in more than 13 languages and offering access to Forex, CFDs, and Options.

We are currently looking for a motivated and client-oriented VIP Account Manager to join our dynamic Sales Team.

\n

Tasks:
Initiate and maintain regular communication with VIP clients via phone and digital channels;
Provide personalized support and promptly resolve VIP client inquiries and requests;
Build long-term relationships with high-value clients and ensure a high level of satisfaction;
Identify clients who meet VIP criteria (deposits, trading volume, activity level) and support their transition to VIP status;
Proactively engage non-VIP clients and encourage account upgrades;
Develop customized strategies to reactivate inactive or low-activity clients;
Monitor client activity and provide tailored recommendations based on trading behavior;
Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of client interactions in the CRM system;
Work closely with internal teams to improve client experience and retention

Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Economics, Business, or a related field;
Fluency in Russian, and English;
Previous experience in client relationship management within financial markets, trading, or fintech;
Strong communication and negotiation skills;
Excellent listening skills and customer-focused mindset;
Proactive, positive, and results-oriented attitude;
Confidence in interacting with high-value clients;
Ability to work with numerical and financial data accurately;
Strong organizational skills and attention to detail.

What we offer:
Remote work model;
Competitive remuneration;
Friendly, enjoyable and positive environment.

\n
With a team of 500+ creative and tech-driven people across the globe, Quadcode is the place where ideas turn into impact, where every project is a chance to grow, innovate, and make your mark.

Join us today, and let's shape the future of fintech together!

Note: All applications will be treated with strict confidence. We thank all applicants for their interest, however, only those candidates selected for interviews will be contacted.

